12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 82 O.S. 2021, Section 1020.7, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 1020.7. Any person intending to use groundwater shall
16 make application apply to the Oklahoma Water Resources Board for an
17 appropriate permit as provided in Section 1020.11 of this title
18 before commencing any drilling for such purposes and before taking
19 water from any completed well heretofore drilled. Such application
20 to take and use groundwater shall be on a form provided by the Board
21 and pursuant to the rules and regulations established by the Board,
22 and shall include documentation that the applicant has a valid,
23 unexpired driver license issued in this state or a valid United
24 States passport.
